Y sé que los tiempos no son como ayer.
Años en esto es que llevo… Y siempre me RENUEVO

A week ago today we picked up Orlando from the airport after his final regular basketball season. 🥹 He’s got just a few more games with the @fibawc at the end of the summer, and then he’s done done. After 14 YEARS. 🤯 The girls and I decided to surprise him at the airport with signs and a decorated car, but when he asked to go to his post-travel fave @mamamargies for bean & cheese 🌮, he had no idea he was playing right into our plan for another surprise: our friends and family joined us for a retirement dinner celebration, and it was the perfect way to kick off a new season of our life. 🥳 Lots of folks have given us great advice for the road ahead, but we know it won’t come without its bumps. The difference is, now we’ll be together. ❤️🏀

“There’s always a way when it comes to real estate”

On this week’s episode, @omv2033 and @hauteintexas  talk about Oscar and Aquila to chat about the importance of PR/marketing, the difficulties of understanding investable capital while playing, as well as their relationship aiding the advancement of their careers.

G I V E A W A Y ! 🎉 Bless @omv2033 for humoring my crazy habit of saying “YES!” to even the most insane experiences. 😂 Tomorrow night we’re stoked to be “celebrity” contestants alongside ACTUAL celebrity chefs at @sacurrent’s fan favorite FLAVOR event, and we’ve got TWO VIP passes to give away so y’all can see how we fare in the culinary showdown! There’s only a handful of GA tickets left, and you don’t wanna miss the best bites in town at the gorgeous @sama_art. It’s the perfect date night - only ours will include a little bit of pressure and a whole lot of competitiveness. 😂

Here’s how to enter:
1) Follow @omv2033 @hauteintexas and @sacurrent
2) Tag who you’re bringing with you in the comments!
3) For an extra entry, share this post to your stories!

Winner must be 21+ and able to attend tomorrow’s event in San Antonio. This contest is not affiliated in any way with Meta or its subsidiaries. Winner will be chosen by noon on May 4th.

Good luck!
Flavor was an absolute great time! It was so awesome competing against these great chefs! Taking home the People's Choice award was the cherry on top!

It’s official, I will be joining Gilley International Group at Keller Williams Portfolio. 

From buying our first home to buying investment properties over the past 12 years in San Antonio I have gained experience and knowledge on both the good and downside of the real estate process. The time has come to serve my community with my knowledge, skills, and services. My goal is to make your real estate experience as positive and smooth as possible. Working diligently with transparency, and building lifelong relationships with our clients. Thank y’all for always supporting my journeys. 

If you or anyone you know is interested in making a move, be it for their personal residence or investment portfolio, please give me a call, send me a message, or email me at 

Orlando@GilleyInternational.com

Very excited to officially announce my new role as an Assistant General Manager for the G-League @capitanescdmx . I am both thrilled and honored for the opportunity to contribute to the success of the team and organization.

Having been part of this organization as a player I have seen the commitment to excellence and community involvement, I am confident that my skills and experience align perfectly with the goals and values of the team. I look forward to contributing my strategic thinking, leadership abilities, and passion for basketball to help drive the team towards continued success both on and off the court.

I am committed to bringing the highest level of professionalism, dedication, and work ethic to my role as Assistant General Manager. I am excited about working closely with our General Manager @mainernick coaching staff, and players to develop a winning culture and achieve the goals we have set for the team.

I have been wearing two hats and will continue to do so. I will continue my passion and dedication I have for real estate with Gilley International Group

social_posts.post_text: Back in 2011 I started my real estate journey, we started buying condos in the medical center area of San Antonio. We quickly saw a demand for fully furnished homes for short to mid term tenants. Thanks to my mentor and his guidance he helped me see the potential in real estate and the wealth it creates. Nothing instant, nothing flashy, just the slow gratification. Fast forward to 2024, I had the distinct honor to help my mentor add another property into his real estate portfolio. 🏡

Truly grateful for the trust and support from our clients, we value you. 

Thank you for choosing us and for giving us the chance to grow together. 

We are seeing a lot more activity in the market. Interest rates are dropping. 

***PM me if you want more info
🏡 Texas Real Estate Agent @gilleyinternationalgroup                                       🏀 Assistant GM @capitanescdmx
